        <!-- Slide 18: Q&A -->
        <div class="slide">
            <div class="slide-number">18</div>
            <h1>Questions & Discussion</h1>
            <h2>Common Questions</h2>

            <h3>‚ùì How does MirrorMaker handle schema evolution?</h3>
            <p><strong>Answer:</strong> MirrorMaker 2 automatically replicates schema registry contents, maintaining version compatibility and supporting backward/forward compatibility rules.</p>

            <h3>‚ùì What happens during network failures?</h3>
            <p><strong>Answer:</strong> MirrorMaker includes automatic retry mechanisms, exponential backoff, and will resume replication once connectivity is restored without data loss.</p>

            <h3>‚ùì Can we replicate specific topics only?</h3>
            <p><strong>Answer:</strong> Yes, topic selection is configurable using regex patterns. You can replicate all topics (.*) or specific patterns (customer.*, transaction.*).</p>

            <h3>‚ùì How do we handle sensitive data?</h3>
            <p><strong>Answer:</strong> All data is encrypted in transit using mTLS. For additional security, implement application-level encryption for sensitive payloads.</p>

            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h4>üí¨ Open Floor for Questions</h4>
                <p><em>Please use the chat or unmute to ask questions</em></p>
            </div>
